<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-17712] Remove javadocs step from CI and release process</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17712</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the javadocs step is both:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Taking up jenkins cycles and generating a &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-cassandra.apache.org/job/Cassandra-trunk-artifacts/1313/jdk=jdk_1.8_latest,label=cassandra/consoleFull&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;large output&lt;/a&gt; in CI when building artifacts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Failing randomly on javadoc issues such as &lt;tt&gt;AlterTableStatement.java:135: error: text not allowed in element&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Apidocs are not being bundled, uploaded or used anywhere. Hence it would be best to remove javadocs generation on every CI. Mainly removing javadoc from artifacts and mvn-install.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
